[[File:Zhao_Baotong_PLAAF.jpg|250px|thumb|Zhao Baotong during the Korean War.]] '''Zhao Baotong''' ({{zh|s=赵宝桐}}, 1928 in [[Fushun]], [[Liaoning]] - 2003) was a [[MiG-15]] pilot of the [[People's Republic of China]]. He was a [[flying ace]] during the [[Korean War]], with 9 victories.<ref name="Var44">{{harvnb|Varhola|2000|p=44}}</ref>
A member of the [[3rd Fighter Aviation Division (People's Republic of China)|3rd Fighter Aviation Division]],<ref name="xinhua_sun">{{cite | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2003-10/25/content_1142512.htm | title = 空中突击手孙生禄 (Sun Shenlu: The Aerial Vanguard) | publisher = [[Xinhua]] | location = Beijing, China | date = 2003-10-25 | accessdate = 2011-08-29|language=zh}}</ref><ref name="Zhang149">{{harvnb|Zhang|2004|p=149}}.</ref> He was the first Chinese Korean War pilot to achieve ace status.<ref name="Zhang149"/> Also known as Chao Bao Tun.<ref name="Var44"/>
Although all Chinese aces have received the title [[Hero's Medal|Combat Hero]] in acknowledgement of their services,<ref name="xinhua_fan">{{cite | url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/politics/2010-10/26/c_12703695_6.htm | title = 中华英雄鏖战世界强敌 抗美援朝"战斗英雄"全景扫描 (Profiles on Combat Heroes During the Korean War) | publisher = [[Xinhua]] | location = Beijing, China | date = 2010-10-26 | accessdate = 2011-08-29|language=zh}}</ref> very little information is known of the Chinese pilots during the war due to the lack of published records.
